@returns(200) {EngineVersions: [EngineVersion]?, Marker: str?}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Lists categories for all event source types, or, if specified, for a specified source type. You can see a list of the event categories and source types in Working with Events and Notifications in the Database Migration Service User Guide.
@optional {SourceType: str, Filters: [Filter]}
@returns(200) {EventCategoryGroupList: [EventCategoryGroup]?}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Lists all the event subscriptions for a customer account. The description of a subscription includes SubscriptionName, SNSTopicARN, CustomerID, SourceType, SourceID, CreationTime, and Status.  If you specify SubscriptionName, this action lists the description for that subscription.
@optional {SubscriptionName: str, Filters: [Filter], MaxRecords: int, Marker: str}
@returns(200) {Marker: str?, EventSubscriptionsList: [EventSubscription]?}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Lists events for a given source identifier and source type. You can also specify a start and end time. For more information on DMS events, see Working with Events and Notifications in the Database Migration Service User Guide.
@optional {SourceIdentifier: str, SourceType: str, StartTime: str(timestamp), EndTime: str(timestamp), Duration: int, EventCategories: [str], Filters: [Filter], MaxRecords: int, Marker: str}
@returns(200) {Marker: str?, Events: [Event]?}

@endpoint POST /
@desc Returns a paginated list of extension pack associations for the specified migration project. An extension pack is an add-on module that emulates functions present in a source database that are required when converting objects to the target database.
